<p>As explained <a href="https://github.com/spring-projects/aws-maven" rel="nofollow">here</a>, it must be pretty simple to deploy maven generated artifacts to Amazon S3 bucket. However I faced 'NoSuchBucket' exception.</p>  <p>The buckets are created in Sydney region and these are snippets of my settings.xml and pom.xml files.</p>  <p>settings.xml:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;server&gt;  &lt;id&gt;aws-release&lt;/id&gt;  &lt;username&gt;Access Key Id&lt;/username&gt;  &lt;password&gt;Secret Access Key&lt;/password&gt; &lt;/server&gt;  &lt;server&gt;  &lt;id&gt;aws-snapshot&lt;/id&gt;  &lt;username&gt;Access Key Id&lt;/username&gt;  &lt;password&gt;Secret Access Key&lt;/password&gt; &lt;/server&gt; </code></pre>  <p>pom.xml:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;distributionManagement&gt;  &lt;repository&gt;   &lt;id&gt;aws-release&lt;/id&gt;   &lt;name&gt;AWS Release Repository&lt;/name&gt;   &lt;url&gt;s3://release.kia.repo-s3-southeast-2.amazonaws.com&lt;/url&gt;  &lt;/repository&gt;   &lt;snapshotRepository&gt;   &lt;id&gt;aws-snapshot&lt;/id&gt;   &lt;name&gt;AWS Snapshot Repository&lt;/name&gt;   &lt;url&gt;s3://snapshots.kia.repo.s3-southeast-2.amazonaws.com&lt;/url&gt;  &lt;/snapshotRepository&gt; &lt;/distributionManagement&gt;  &lt;build&gt;  &lt;extensions&gt;   &lt;extension&gt;     &lt;groupId&gt;org.springframework.build&lt;/groupId&gt;     &lt;artifactId&gt;aws-maven&lt;/artifactId&gt;     &lt;version&gt;5.0.0.RELEASE&lt;/version&gt;   &lt;/extension&gt;  &lt;/extensions&gt; &lt;/build&gt; </code></pre>  <p>This is the error:</p>  <pre><code>[ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.apache.maven.plugins:maven-deploy-plugin:2.7:deploy (default-deploy) on project simple_s3: Failed to retrieve remote metadata aws:simple_s3:1.0-SNAPSHOT/maven-metadata.xml: Could not transfer metadata aws:simple_s3:1.0-SNAPSHOT/maven-metadata.xml from/to aws-snapshot (s3://snapshots.kia.repo.s3-southeast-2.amazonaws.com): Status Code: 404, AWS Service: Amazon S3, AWS Request ID: 6FE0FE5F23820826, AWS Error Code: NoSuchBucket, AWS Error Message: The specified bucket does not exist </code></pre>  <p>And these are <a href="https://kiazam.wordpress.com/2015/10/04/how-to-get-maven-deploy-plugin-to-deploy-to-amazon-s3-bucket/" rel="nofollow">the steps</a> that I followed to create the buckets and set the permissions.</p>  <p>I would appreciate your suggestions.</p>